{{Infobox language |name=Lamas Quechua |altname=San Martín Quechua |nativename= |states=[[Perú]] |speakers=15,000 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Quechua languages|Quechua]] |fam2=[[Quechua II]] |fam3=[[Northern Quechua|Northern]] |fam4=[[Lowland Peruvian Quechua|Lowland Peruvian]] |iso3=qvs |glotto=sanm1289 |glottorefname=San Martin Quechua }}
'''Lamas''' or '''San Martín Quechua''' (''Lamista, Llakwash Runashimi'') is a variety of [[Quechua languages|Quechua]] spoken in the provinces of [[Lamas Province|Lamas]] in the [[Peru]]vian region of [[San Martin Region|San Martin]] and in some villages on the river [[Huallaga River|Huallaga]] in the region of [[Ucayali Region|Ucayali]].
Lamas Quechua belongs to [[Quechua II]], subgroup II-B ([[Lowland Peruvian Quechua]]).
